@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<link rel="stylesheet" href="~/css/beneficiarycreatecss.css" />

<div class="hw-page-head">
    <div>
        <div class="hw-page-eyebrow">
            <i class="bi bi-shield-check"></i> Legal & Compliance
        </div>
        <h1 class="hw-page-title">Privacy <span>Policy</span></h1>
        <p class="hw-page-desc">
            HWSETA Impact Hub privacy notice for beneficiaries, administrators, programme teams, and authorised stakeholders.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="hw-card">
    <div class="hw-card-head">
        <div class="hw-card-icon green">
            <i class="bi bi-lock"></i>
        </div>
        <div>
            <div class="hw-card-title">1. Introduction</div>
            <div class="hw-card-sub">How your personal information is handled in HWSETA Impact Hub</div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="hw-card-body">
        <p>
            HWSETA Impact Hub is a beneficiary management, enrolment, monitoring, communication, and reporting platform
            used to support programme administration, beneficiary onboarding, form collection, status tracking, and related
            operational processes.
        </p>
        <p>
            This Privacy Policy explains how personal information is collected, used, stored, shared, and protected when
            beneficiaries, administrators, programme managers, and other authorised users access and use the platform.
        </p>
        <p>
            HWSETA is committed to handling personal information lawfully, fairly, and securely, and to complying with the
            Protection of Personal Information Act, 2013 (“POPIA”), as well as other applicable legal and regulatory obligations.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="hw-card" style="margin-top:18px;">
    <div class="hw-card-head">
        <div class="hw-card-icon gold">
            <i class="bi bi-database"></i>
        </div>
        <div>
            <div class="hw-card-title">2. Information We Collect</div>
            <div class="hw-card-sub">Categories of personal and operational data processed by the platform</div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="hw-card-body">
        <p>The platform may collect and process the following categories of information:</p>

        <ul class="hw-tip-list">
            <li class="hw-tip-item">
                <i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill"></i>
                <span><strong>Identity information</strong>, including first name, middle name, surname, identifier type, ID number or passport number, and date of birth.</span>
            </li>
            <li class="hw-tip-item">
                <i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill"></i>
                <span><strong>Demographic information</strong>, including gender, race, citizenship status, disability status, disability type, education level, and employment status.</span>
            </li>
            <li class="hw-tip-item">
                <i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill"></i>
                <span><strong>Contact information</strong>, including email address, mobile number, alternative number, and address details.</span>
            </li>
            <li class="hw-tip-item">
                <i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill"></i>
                <span><strong>Programme and enrolment information</strong>, including cohorts, providers, employers, qualification types, funding types, enrolment statuses, and related history.</span>
            </li>
            <li class="hw-tip-item">
                <i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill"></i>
                <span><strong>Form and submission information</strong>, including monitoring forms, form answers, supporting declarations, and operational workflow data.</span>
            </li>
            <li class="hw-tip-item">
                <i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill"></i>
                <span><strong>Communication information</strong>, including system messages, feedback, notifications, form invitations, and communication thread history.</span>
            </li>
            <li class="hw-tip-item">
                <i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill"></i>
                <span><strong>Document and upload information</strong>, including uploaded supporting documents, completion letters, and metadata related to uploaded files.</span>
            </li>
            <li class="hw-tip-item">
                <i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill"></i>
                <span><strong>System and security information</strong>, including user accounts, roles, timestamps, audit trail entries, IP-related request data, and usage logs required for security, support, and compliance.</span>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="hw-card" style="margin-top:18px;">
    <div class="hw-card-head">
        <div class="hw-card-icon dark">
            <i class="bi bi-gear"></i>
        </div>
        <div>
            <div class="hw-card-title">3. Why We Process Personal Information</div>
            <div class="hw-card-sub">Purposes for which information is collected and used</div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="hw-card-body">
        <p>Personal information is processed for legitimate operational, contractual, and legal purposes, including to:</p>

        <ul class="hw-tip-list">
            <li class="hw-tip-item"><i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill"></i><span>register, verify, and manage beneficiaries and authorised system users;</span></li>
            <li class="hw-tip-item"><i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill"></i><span>administer programmes, cohorts, enrolments, providers, employers, and related records;</span></li>
            <li class="hw-tip-item"><i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill"></i><span>create, publish, send, receive, and process digital forms and submissions;</span></li>
            <li class="hw-tip-item"><i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill"></i><span>enable communication between administrators, programme teams, and beneficiaries;</span></li>
            <li class="hw-tip-item"><i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill"></i><span>send notifications, invitations, reminders, updates, and service-related communications by email, SMS, or in-app channels;</span></li>
            <li class="hw-tip-item"><i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill"></i><span>maintain audit trails, reporting, accountability, security monitoring, and operational oversight;</span></li>
            <li class="hw-tip-item"><i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill"></i><span>meet legal, regulatory, funding, governance, and reporting obligations;</span></li>
            <li class="hw-tip-item"><i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill"></i><span>protect the integrity, confidentiality, and availability of the platform and its records.</span></li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="hw-card" style="margin-top:18px;">
    <div class="hw-card-head">
        <div class="hw-card-icon green">
            <i class="bi bi-journal-check"></i>
        </div>
        <div>
            <div class="hw-card-title">4. Lawful Basis for Processing</div>
            <div class="hw-card-sub">How processing is justified</div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="hw-card-body">
        <p>Personal information is processed on one or more of the following lawful grounds:</p>
        <ul class="hw-tip-list">
            <li class="hw-tip-item"><i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill"></i><span>the data subject’s consent, where consent is required;</span></li>
            <li class="hw-tip-item"><i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill"></i><span>the conclusion or performance of an agreement or programme participation process;</span></li>
            <li class="hw-tip-item"><i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill"></i><span>compliance with legal and regulatory obligations;</span></li>
            <li class="hw-tip-item"><i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill"></i><span>legitimate administrative, governance, security, and reporting interests of HWSETA and authorised stakeholders.</span></li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="hw-card" style="margin-top:18px;">
    <div class="hw-card-head">
        <div class="hw-card-icon gold">
            <i class="bi bi-share"></i>
        </div>
        <div>
            <div class="hw-card-title">5. Sharing of Information</div>
            <div class="hw-card-sub">When data may be disclosed</div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="hw-card-body">
        <p>Personal information may be shared only where necessary and authorised, including with:</p>
        <ul class="hw-tip-list">
            <li class="hw-tip-item"><i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill"></i><span>internal HWSETA administrators, programme managers, authorised reviewers, and approved support personnel;</span></li>
            <li class="hw-tip-item"><i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill"></i><span>approved training providers, employers, or implementation partners where operationally required;</span></li>
            <li class="hw-tip-item"><i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill"></i><span>service providers supporting hosting, messaging, document storage, or technical operations under confidentiality and security obligations;</span></li>
            <li class="hw-tip-item"><i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill"></i><span>regulators, funders, auditors, or public bodies where disclosure is required by law, policy, funding framework, or audit obligation.</span></li>
        </ul>

        <p>
            Information is not sold to third parties. Access is restricted according to user role, business need, and
            authorised process scope.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="hw-card" style="margin-top:18px;">
    <div class="hw-card-head">
        <div class="hw-card-icon dark">
            <i class="bi bi-shield-lock"></i>
        </div>
        <div>
            <div class="hw-card-title">6. Information Security</div>
            <div class="hw-card-sub">How information is protected</div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="hw-card-body">
        <p>HWSETA Impact Hub uses appropriate technical and organisational measures to protect information, including:</p>

        <ul class="hw-tip-list">
            <li class="hw-tip-item"><i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill"></i><span>role-based access control and authenticated user access;</span></li>
            <li class="hw-tip-item"><i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill"></i><span>encryption and protected storage of sensitive fields where implemented in the platform;</span></li>
            <li class="hw-tip-item"><i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill"></i><span>audit trails, activity logging, and change history for accountability;</span></li>
            <li class="hw-tip-item"><i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill"></i><span>controlled upload and document handling mechanisms;</span></li>
            <li class="hw-tip-item"><i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill"></i><span>security monitoring, password-based access controls, and system administration safeguards.</span></li>
        </ul>

        <p>
            Although reasonable safeguards are applied, no online platform can guarantee absolute security. Users must also
            protect their login credentials and report suspected unauthorised access immediately.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="hw-card" style="margin-top:18px;">
    <div class="hw-card-head">
        <div class="hw-card-icon green">
            <i class="bi bi-clock-history"></i>
        </div>
        <div>
            <div class="hw-card-title">7. Retention of Information</div>
            <div class="hw-card-sub">How long information may be kept</div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="hw-card-body">
        <p>
            Personal information will be retained only for as long as necessary to fulfil programme, operational, legal,
            reporting, contractual, and audit requirements. Retention periods may vary depending on record type, applicable
            policy, or statutory requirement.
        </p>
        <p>
            Where records are no longer required, they will be securely deleted, de-identified, archived, or disposed of in
            accordance with applicable record management and legal obligations.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="hw-card" style="margin-top:18px;">
    <div class="hw-card-head">
        <div class="hw-card-icon gold">
            <i class="bi bi-person-vcard"></i>
        </div>
        <div>
            <div class="hw-card-title">8. Rights of Data Subjects</div>
            <div class="hw-card-sub">Your rights in relation to your personal information</div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="hw-card-body">
        <p>Subject to applicable law and process requirements, a data subject may have the right to:</p>
        <ul class="hw-tip-list">
            <li class="hw-tip-item"><i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill"></i><span>request access to personal information held about them;</span></li>
            <li class="hw-tip-item"><i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill"></i><span>request correction or updating of inaccurate or incomplete information;</span></li>
            <li class="hw-tip-item"><i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill"></i><span>object to certain forms of processing where legally permitted;</span></li>
            <li class="hw-tip-item"><i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill"></i><span>request deletion or restriction of processing where appropriate and legally permissible;</span></li>
            <li class="hw-tip-item"><i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill"></i><span>withdraw consent where processing is based on consent, subject to legal and operational limitations.</span></li>
        </ul>

        <p>
            Requests may be limited where retention, auditability, legal compliance, contractual obligations, or public-interest
            functions require continued processing.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="hw-card" style="margin-top:18px;">
    <div class="hw-card-head">
        <div class="hw-card-icon dark">
            <i class="bi bi-chat-square-text"></i>
        </div>
        <div>
            <div class="hw-card-title">9. Communications, Forms, and Feedback</div>
            <div class="hw-card-sub">Special handling of chats, form submissions, and operational messages</div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="hw-card-body">
        <p>
            The platform may record communication history, message threads, feedback submissions, form invitations, and form
            responses to support case management, beneficiary support, workflow tracking, auditability, and service delivery.
        </p>
        <p>
            Information submitted through monitoring forms, update forms, registration forms, or related digital workflows may
            be used to update beneficiary records, programme tracking data, communication status, and reporting information,
            depending on the purpose of the form and the administrative process it supports.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="hw-card" style="margin-top:18px;">
    <div class="hw-card-head">
        <div class="hw-card-icon green">
            <i class="bi bi-globe"></i>
        </div>
        <div>
            <div class="hw-card-title">10. Cross-Border or Third-Party Services</div>
            <div class="hw-card-sub">Use of hosting and communication services</div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="hw-card-body">
        <p>
            Where third-party infrastructure or communication services are used, HWSETA will take reasonable steps to ensure
            that such providers are subject to appropriate confidentiality, security, and processing obligations.
        </p>
        <p>
            Cross-border processing, if any, will be managed in line with legal requirements and appropriate safeguards.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="hw-card" style="margin-top:18px;">
    <div class="hw-card-head">
        <div class="hw-card-icon gold">
            <i class="bi bi-arrow-repeat"></i>
        </div>
        <div>
            <div class="hw-card-title">11. Updates to This Policy</div>
            <div class="hw-card-sub">Changes to the privacy notice</div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="hw-card-body">
        <p>
            This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time to reflect changes in law, policy, operational requirements,
            or system functionality. The latest published version on the platform will apply from its effective date.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="hw-card" style="margin-top:18px; margin-bottom:24px;">
    <div class="hw-card-head">
        <div class="hw-card-icon dark">
            <i class="bi bi-envelope-paper"></i>
        </div>
        <div>
            <div class="hw-card-title">12. Contact and Queries</div>
            <div class="hw-card-sub">How to raise privacy-related questions</div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="hw-card-body">
        <p>
            Questions, requests, or concerns relating to privacy, data handling, or access to personal information may be
            directed through the official HWSETA support or compliance channels made available by the organisation.
        </p>

        <div style="margin-top:14px;padding:14px 16px;border:1px solid var(--hw-border);border-radius:12px;background:var(--hw-offwhite);">
            <div><strong>Application:</strong> HWSETA Impact Hub</div>
            <div><strong>Owner:</strong> Health and Welfare Sector Education and Training Authority</div>
            <div><strong>Purpose:</strong> Beneficiary management, enrolment administration, monitoring, communication, and reporting</div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>